Ad Text:
Overview

Are you insatiably curious, deeply passionate about the realm of databases and analytics, and ready to tackle complex challenges in a dynamic environment in the era of AI? If so, we invite you to join our team as Cloud & AI - Data Solution Engineer (SE) in Innovative Data Platform for SME&C - Small, Medium Enterprises and Channel business, here at Microsoft. Here, you'll be at the forefront of innovation, working on cutting-edge projects that leverage the latest technologies to drive meaningful impact. Join us and be part of a team that thrives on collaboration, creativity, and continuous learning.

Databases & Analytics is a growth opportunity for Microsoft Azure, as well as its partners and customers. It includes a rich portfolio of products including IaaS and PaaS services on the Azure Platform in the age of AI. These technologies empower customers to build, deploy, and manage database and analytics applications in a cloud-native way.

Responsibilities


As an Innovative Cloud & AI - Data Solution Engineer (SE), you will play a pivotal role in helping our customers unlock the full potential of Microsoft’s cloud database and analytics stack across every stage of deployment.

You’ll collaborate closely with engineering leaders and platform teams to accelerate the Fabric Data Platform, including Azure Databases and Analytics, through hands-on engagements like Proof of Concepts, hackathons, and architecture workshops. This opportunity will allow you to accelerate your career growth, develop deep business acumen, hone your technical skills, and become adept at solution design and deployment.

You’ll guide customers through secure, scalable solution design, influence technical decisions, and accelerate database and analytics migration into their deployment workflows. In summary, you’ll help customers modernize their data platform and realize the full value of Microsoft’s platform, all while enjoying flexible work opportunities.

As a trusted technical advisor, you’ll guide customers through secure, scalable solution design, influence technical decisions, and accelerate database and analytics migration into their deployment workflows. In summary, you’ll help customers modernize their data platform and realize the full value of Microsoft’s platform.

Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others, and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.


Qualifications

Minimum required Qualifications 

Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field AND 4+ years technical pre-sales or technical consulting experience

OR Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field AND 6+ years technical pre-sales or technical consulting experience

OR 7+ years technical pre-sales or technical consulting experience

OR equivalent experience.

4+ years experience on Azure Databases (SQL DB, Cosmos DB, PostgreSQL) from migration & modernize and creating new AI apps.

2+ years experience on Azure Analytics (Fabric, Azure Databricks, Purview) and competitors (BigQuery, Redshift, Snowflake) in data warehouse, data lake, big data, analytics, real-time intelligent, and reporting using integrated Data Security & Governance.

4+ years experience leading technical engagements (e.g., hackathons, PoCs, MVPs) that drive production-scale outcomes.

Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. Hands-on with Snowflake and AWS-native tools (e.g. Glue, S3, Lambda).
Permanent Role| Hybrid working| Attractive salary package

About the Role

The Data Platform Engineering Manager leads the team responsible for designing, developing, and delivering icare’s enterprise data platform and reusable data products. This role is critical to ensuring scalable, secure, and high-performing data capabilities that power insights decision-making, automation, and future AI use cases.

You will oversee the end-to-end development lifecycle – from backlog planning through to tested and automated deployment – while ensuring quality, reusability, and platform alignment. This role also plays a key leadership function in working across teams to shape solutions that enable strategic outcomes for icare.

Benefits

A corporate wellbeing program with subsidised gym membership, free flu vaccinations and health check programs
Comprehensive learning and development support aligned to icare’s Core Capabilities.
Our People Awards - On-the-spot Recognition, Quarterly Values Awards & Our People Annual Awards
Access to our Employee Assistance Program

Duties

It’s an exciting time at icare where no two days are the same; as a Manager, Data Platform Engineering you will:

Lead the engineering team responsible for building data pipelines, models, and reusable components using Snowflake and AWS-native tools (e.g. Glue, S3, Lambda).
Lead the development of modern data platform including analytical feature store, API wrapped data services and enabling embedment of operational analytics into core platforms
Translate business and analytical requirements into well-designed data products, aligned to domain needs and platform strategy.
Oversee the design and delivery of scalable data models, semantic layers, and data marts to support insights and CX solutions.
Embed strong solution design practices and partner with architects to ensure alignment with enterprise patterns.
Manage and coach a multidisciplinary team including Data Engineers, Solution Designers, DevOps Engineers, and Data Test Engineers.
Ensure development standards, best practices, and governance (e.g. naming, logging, lineage) are consistently applied.
Drive adoption of test-driven development, CI/CD, and automation practices across the team.
Collaborate with Data Ops to ensure smooth deployment, observability, and post-release support.
Partner with Performance Monitoring & Insights and CXM Ops teams to ensure platform capabilities meet real-world reporting and customer intelligence needs.
Continuously improve engineering maturity, velocity, and reusability of data products across service lines.
Contribute to GenAI and Agentic AI readiness by building modern, AI-enabled data foundations.

Team Leadership

Inspire and lead a high-performing engineering team, fostering a culture of accountability, technical excellence, and continuous learning.
Collaborate with cross-functional leads across Data Ops, Insights, and CXM, and Governance to support icare’s data strategy.
Support Agile ways of working and contribute to the design of an evolving, service-aligned operating model.

Skills & Experience

7+ years in Data Engineering, including 3+ years in leadership or senior technical role
Proven experience leading Data Engineering or Data Platform teams in complex, cloud-native environments
Demonstrated success in delivering scalable data pipelines and reusable data products
Experience implementing engineering standards, code reviews, and reusable frameworks
Track record of enabling insights, CX, or AI teams through platform engineering
Strong technical knowledge of modern data platforms (Snowflake, AWS)
Deep understanding of data pipeline design, ELT/ETL patterns, and data modelling principles
Proficiency in CI/CD, testing frameworks, and deployment automation
Ability to lead multidisciplinary technical teams across development lifecycles
Excellent stakeholder communication and collaboration skills
Experience setting standards and best practices for engineering teams
Experience in Agile delivery environments, virtual squads, or service-aligned team models
Exposure to real-time data ingestion and event-driven architecture
Contribution to GenAI or advanced analytics-enabling platforms
Familiarity with data mesh or federated data product design
Knowledge of data governance, metadata, and lineage practices
Understanding of public sector or regulated industry environments

Culture

We know our strength comes from the diversity of our people and would encourage people with different experiences and backgrounds to apply. We are committed to our people’s development so the people of NSW can thrive.

About the Company

Our purpose is to care for the people of New South Wales, building confidence and trust so our communities can thrive. As NSW’s agency of insurance and care, in the past year we insured 338,000 businesses, covering four million workers and supporting 92,000 workers with injuries. We cared for over 1,800 people severely injured on our roads and supported more than 5,450 impacted by a dust disease. We helped 775 homeowners, insuring $20.9 billion in residential projects, and continue to protect $436 billion in NSW Government assets including iconic landmarks the Sydney Harbour Bridge and Opera House. icare continues to refine and transform how we deliver services to improve experiences for those we serve.

For more information about icare visit our website

About the Role

As the Solution Architect, you will be responsible for the end-to-end technical architecture of the program, ensuring solutions are scalable, secure, and aligned with business goals and enterprise standards. You will engage closely with the Program Manager, CIO, Product Owners, ICT operations teams and external vendors to design and guide the delivery of modern, cloud-based solutions.

This is a hands-on, influential role where you will translate business requirements into technical designs, oversee solution delivery, and drive best practice across the Microsoft ecosystem.

Roles and Responsibilities:

Lead solution design across Dynamics 365, Power Apps, Power Automate, and Azure

Review and interpret Business Requirements to create cohesive, future-ready technical solutions

Develop architecture artefacts including solution designs, integration patterns, data models, and system diagrams

Work with internal ICT teams and external vendors to ensure architecture quality and alignment

Provide technical leadership and guidance across agile delivery teams

Contribute to the strategic direction of technology investments and enterprise architecture

Key Requirements:

7+ years' experience in solution/technical architecture within enterprise environments

Strong expertise across the Microsoft technology stack (Dynamics 365, Power Platform, Azure)

Proven ability to design and govern complex, integrated cloud solutions

Experience working with large delivery partners and managing multi-vendor environments

Strong documentation, modelling, and architectural governance capability

Public Sector experience is essential

Why Smart?

Look forward to working with Australia's leading and most trusted provider of Employee Management Services, making the benefits of salary packaging, novated leasing, and fleet management readily available to employers and their employees.

Working at Smart offers more than a job. It is a dynamic workplace that matches the enthusiasm for the work you do and ambition for an exciting fast-paced career. We have all been hired for a purpose and a reason.

Every day you will be part of a team that helps support fellow Australians - many working in essential services, corporates, government, and not-for-profits - to take home more money in their pay packets.

Do you have what it takes to become a Senior AI Engineer?

We're looking for a highly skilled Senior AI Engineer to join our AI Squad. You'll help design, build, and operate production-grade AI systems that drive real business impact. The role requires strong engineering foundations, deep experience with Azure, and the ability to work across data, application, and AI layers.

Key responsibilities:

Build and operate AI services and APIs for inference and retrieval (LLMs, RAG, ML models, agents) based on established designs and architectural guidance.
Develop secure, reliable data pipelines for training, retrieval, and evaluation, with clear governance, privacy, and audit expectations.
Contribute to the AI platform and MLOps toolchain: CI/CD for models, feature stores, model registry, experiment tracking, monitoring, and automated rollback.
Translate functional requirements into technical tasks; estimate effort and deliver to agreed success criteria.
Write clean, well-tested code in .NET and Python, following shared patterns and participating in reviews.
Run AI workloads in production with clear SLIs/SLOs for availability, latency, and cost; escalate and manage incidents effectively.
Apply security-by-design principles across all AI solutions, including prompt protections, data minimisation, content filtering, and robust access controls.
Maintain documentation, runbooks, and architectural decision records; contribute to reusable reference implementations.

Job Title: Snr Data Engineer - up to $180K base - 2:3 hybrid in Mac Park
Ad Text:
The company

A well regarded business in the finance sector. They have grown rapidly over the last 5 years, and continue to grow.

They are based in the heart of Macquarie Park and are close to the metro station. Great offices, but they also offer plenty of scope to WFH (2 days a week in the office: 3 WFH).

The role

The company continues to strengthen and further their data engineering & analytics capacities create further insights to shape the ongoing growth and evolution of of the business.

They are a cloud centric Microsoft shop that's very modern. They do though still run a data warehouse on a VM that they are now looking to upgrade to Fabric running on Azure. 

The data engineer will be there to primarily design, develop data & evolve the data wrangling stuctures around Fabric, Data Lake & Data Factory, and assist with the data modelling, which will be done along the lines of medallion architecture . This is a senior role within the data team. As such you'd be expected to be able to contribute at an architectural level, interface with business stakeholders and help mentor junior engineers. .

So we're looking for senior engineers with a strong history in the Azure space, who are friendly team players. MS/Azure Certs would be well regarded. MS Fabric skills are a must have

What's in it for you?

A really healthy salary (up to $180K base plus super plus a bonus)
Plenty of scope to WFH
A blue chip tech stack
A great workplace culture - friendly, welcoming & supportive
Offices close to the Metro (parking and buses also nearby)

If that sounds like the role for you, apply now!
